    dc:creator "Garavello, Júlio C.; Britski, Heraldo A.; Birindelli, José L. O." ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of Leporinus jamesi (Characiformes: Anostomidae), a poorly known species of Leporinus from the lowlands of the central Amazon, Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551187>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551181>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551185> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551187>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. (a) Roetter’s drawing of Leporinus jamesi based on holotype MCZ 20439, 73.8 mm SL, rio Solimões at Manacapuru, and published in Borodin (1929: plate 9); (b) Leporinus jamesi, MUSM 29750, 132.1 mm SL, Peru; (c) Leporinus octomaculatus, upper rio Paraguay basin, photographed live by Claudio Zawadzki." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4551187/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551181>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. SEM image of jaws of Leporinus jamesi, lateral view, MZUSP 75639, 89.0 mm SL. The dotted line indicates a fourth tooth that is normally present, but that was lost during preparation of the specimen. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4551181/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551185>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Map of northern South American showing the distribution of Leporinus jamesi. White symbol represents the type locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4551185/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

